Gauteng police are searching for three suspects after a security guard was shot dead in Diepsloot on Tuesday morning. Police spokesperson Col Mavela Masondo said the 38-year-old man was killed  during a "cross-pavement robbery" at a mall in extension 10. "The deceased had allegedly just collected cash from a shop when he was accosted. He was allegedly pushed to the ground by one of the suspects, before he was shot three times. "They made off with a bag of cash in a white bakkie," Masondo said, adding that an investigation was under way. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to theÂ Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.